<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="483" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,423,1411,1437]" box="[151,423,1411,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,423,1411,1437]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,423,1411,1437]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">
<taxonomicName box="[151,342,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Celaenorrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Celaenorrhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1481,1758]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">
Our treatment of this group as 
<taxonomicName box="[500,675,1481,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Celaenorrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[500,675,1481,1506]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Celaenorrhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation author="Cock" box="[745,1025,1481,1506]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" refString="Cock, M. J. W. &amp; Congdon, T. C. E. (2011 b) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 3. Pyrginae: Celaenorrhinini. Zootaxa, 3033, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">Cock &amp; Congdon 2011b</bibRefCitation>
) needs to be revisited in light of the detailed work of 
<bibRefCitation author="Libert" box="[351,505,1517,1542]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" refString="Libert, M. (2014) Sur la taxonomie du genre Celaenorrhinus Hubner en Afrique (Lepidoptera, Hesperiidae). M. J. B. S. A. S. - Librairie Top Duck, Amboise, France, 272 pp., 26 pl." type="book" year="2014">Libert (2014)</bibRefCitation>
on this genus, which resulted in the recognition of four genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Celaenorrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1436,1517,1542]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Celaenorrhinus</emphasis>
HÃ¼bner
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1911" box="[250,437,1553,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[250,353,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Apallaga</emphasis>
Strand
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Libert" authorityName="Libert" box="[451,657,1553,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scopulifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[451,580,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Scopulifera</emphasis>
Libert
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Libert. Life" authorityName="Libert. Life" box="[716,975,1553,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bettonula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[716,825,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Bettonula</emphasis>
Libert. Life
</taxonomicName>
histories have not been documented for any species of 
<taxonomicName box="[318,447,1589,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Scopulifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,447,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Scopulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[502,611,1589,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bettonula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,611,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Bettonula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as yet. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cock" box="[706,1000,1589,1614]" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" refString="Cock, M. J. W. &amp; Congdon, T. C. E. (2011 b) Observations on the biology of Afrotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera) principally from Kenya. Part 3. Pyrginae: Celaenorrhinini. Zootaxa, 3033, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">Cock &amp; Congdon (2011b)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the limited number of pupae known for this group can be divided into those that are brown with cephalic horns, and those that are green with only a trace of a frontal protuberance; the former correspond with 
<taxonomicName box="[984,1159,1661,1686]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Celaenorrhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[984,1159,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Celaenorrhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and the latter with 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1911" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,254,1697,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,254,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Apallaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. We also noted that the pupa of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wallengren)" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1911" box="[676,953,1697,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mokeezi">
<emphasis box="[676,798,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">A. mokeezi</emphasis>
(Wallengren)
</taxonomicName>
differs from other green pupae in that it is covered with white powder; 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1911" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1911" box="[471,592,1733,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mokeezi">
<emphasis box="[471,592,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">A. mokeezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises a monophyletic clade within the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1911" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1911" box="[1158,1261,1733,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Apallaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1261,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="483">Apallaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
